{ 10 }is appropriate if10is meant to be an element value. If10is meant to be an argument to a non-list constructor of a container, use direct initialization.Best practiceWhen constructing a container (or any type that has a list constructor) with initializers that are not element values, use direct initialization.TipWhen astd::vectoris a member of a class type, it is not obvious how to provide a default initializer that sets the length of astd::vectorto some initial value:#include <vector>

